===============================================================
[2026-03-03] [POST-BUILD] [DECISION] [6 PROPOSED GAPS ANALYSIS]
===============================================================

## Context
Evaluated 6 proposed "gaps" against spec.md, design.md, and implemented
codebase to determine which are real gaps vs. hallucinated or misattributed.

## Analysis Results

| # | Gap | Real Gap? | Action |
|---|-----|-----------|--------|
| 1 | Cognitive Schema Bridge (BUP Git patches) | No | None |
| 2 | Agent-Kit SDK (OpenClaw Middleware) | No | None |
| 3 | Agent Capabilities Registry | No (feature request) | Deferred |
| 4 | Event-Driven Webhook Registry | No (intentional design) | None |
| 5 | Coalition Mode | No (not in spec) | None |
| 6 | Structured Argument Graph Endpoint | Partially | Deferred |

## Breakdown

### Items 1, 2, 5 — Conflate OpenClaw internals with platform concerns
- HARD_CORE.md/PROTECTIVE_BELT.md are not platform files; hard core and
  protective belt are text fields on DebateParticipant
- "Git-style patches" is a frontend UI metaphor, not a data format
- L3/L5 memory layers are OpenClaw-internal — spec says agents are black boxes
- SDK/middleware for one agent framework violates black-box principle
- Coalition/sub-agent hierarchies are internal to agents, invisible to platform

### Item 4 — Contradicts documented architectural decision
- design.md Section 4.4 explicitly chose polling over webhooks
- Agents already have WebSocket option for near-real-time observation
- No callback_url field exists on any model (confirmed across all 8 model files)

### Items 3, 6 — Valid feature requests, not spec gaps
- Capabilities registry: Agent.model_info JSONB already provides informal signals;
  Thesis Board provides formal capability demonstration
- Argument graph endpoint: data exists in GraphNode/GraphEdge with source_debate_id
  linkage; GET /graph/nodes can be filtered; dedicated endpoint would be UX
  improvement but not a missing spec requirement

## Decisions Made
- All 6 items rejected as implementation gaps — none require code changes
- Items 3 and 6 logged to post-MVP backlog as optional feature requests
- No code modified, no tests affected

## Verification
- Cross-referenced each claim against spec.md, design.md, and codebase
- Confirmed no callback_url, capabilities, group_id, or coalition fields exist
- Confirmed BUP JSON schema already machine-parseable (Section 10)
- Confirmed polling model documented in design.md Section 4.4

